{"title": "Unwanted Healing", "content": "You are afflicted with a terrible illness, oh no! Is it bad? Likely. Luckily a friend or the local doctor has the treatment for your condition. But what is that? You have no interest in undergoing it despite knowing it will heal you? Why is that?\n\nMost people that are sick will wind up taking whatever antidote or treatment they need in a heartbeat. However there are those who for whatever ridiculous reason will turn it down. These reasons may be various, ranging from simply not trusting the treatment, a Greater Need Than Mine, being Afraid of Doctors, to the healing literally harming them. Regardless, they have to take it, even if it means methods like slipping the medicine into food or pinning them down and performing it by force. The alternative can range from prolonged suffering or worst case scenario: a slow, agonizing death.\n\nSee also Afraid of Needles, Unwanted Revival and Unwanted Rescue. May result in a Mercy Kill if the person would prefer death over treatment.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnwantedHealing", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JojosBizarreAdventureStardustCrusaders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OreTachiNoPartyWaMachigatteiru", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/SwordArtOnline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/RainbowRowellsRunaways", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/KungFuPanda2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Deadpool2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HanselAndGretelWitchHunters", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MontyPythonsLifeOfBrian", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ElChapulinColorado", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Friends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThePassage", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Scrubs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/OneThousandWaysToDie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Supernatural", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheNextGener